    <body>
      <group id="content" extype="content">
        <trans-unit id="101" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve" extradata="MT" restype="x-metadata">
          <source>Define new departments</source>
        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="102" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve" extradata="MT" restype="x-metadata">
          <source>Departments are operating units that represent a functional area of a business, such as sales or accounting.</source>
        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="103" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>Define new departments</source>
        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="104" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>Departments are operating units that represent a functional area of a business, such as sales or accounting.</source>
        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="105" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>Many companies have organizational hierarchies that display the various departments within a business.</source>
        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="106" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>This procedure walks through the process of creating departments, and adding those departments to an organizations departmental hierarchy.</source>
        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="107" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>The demo data company used to create this procedure is USMF.</source>
        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="108" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>Go to Human resources &gt; Departments &gt; Departments.</source>
        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="109" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>Click New to open the drop dialog.</source>
        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="110" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>In the Name field, type a value.</source>
        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="111" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>Example: Project billing</source>
        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="112" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>In the Memo field, type a value.</source>
        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="113" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>Example: Project billing</source>
        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="114" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>In the Manager field, enter or select a value.</source>
        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="115" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>Example: Jodi Christiansen</source>
        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="116" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>Click Save.</source>
        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="117" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>Close the page.</source>
        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="118" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>Go to Human resources &gt; Departments &gt; Department hierarchy.</source>
        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="119" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>Click Edit.</source>
        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="120" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>Click Insert.</source>
        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="121" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>Click Department.</source>
        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="122" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>In the list, find and select the desired record.</source>
        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="123" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>Example: Project billing</source>
        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="124" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>Click OK.</source>
        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="125" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>Click Publish to open the drop dialog.</source>
        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="126" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>In the Effective date field, enter a date and time.</source>
        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="127" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>When publishing the department hierarchy, you can select when to make the changes effective.</source>
        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="128" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>Changes can be future dated.</source>
        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="129" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>For example, you may know that at the beginning of your fiscal year you will be adding an additional department.</source>
        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="130" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>You can set your effective date to the beginning of the fiscal year, and the changes to the hierarchy will be effective on that date.</source>
        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="131" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>In the Describe changes field, type a value.</source>
        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="132" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>Click Publish.</source>
        </trans-unit>
